Here's how you can write the `clean_column` function in Julia.

```julia
function clean_column(col)
    # Lowercase column name
    col = lowercase(col);

    # Replace any leading or trailing whitespaces with nothing
    col = replace(col, " "^* => "");
    col = replace(col, " $" => "");

    # Replace spaces and hyphens with an underscore
    col = replace(col, "-" => "_");
    col = replace(col, " " => "_");

    return col;
end
```
This function first converts the input column name to lowercase. Then it removes any leading or trailing spaces from the string using regular expressions. After that, it replaces all spaces and hyphens with underscores. Finally, it returns the cleaned column name.
